main event: A witness in Takoma Park, Maryland observed a coppery-colored object with two red lights on top and one white light underneath on July 22, 1966.
interesting points: The object came on suddenly from the east and disappeared to the south.
The two bright red lights appeared to have a slight pulsating or flickering movement.
The object also appeared to have a slight exhaust trail.
The sighting is consistent with that of an aircraft sighting.
The witness described the object as moving faster than a satellite, disappearing in 2-3 seconds.
